  "prompt": "I'm going to a wedding that my boyfriend is in, I'm a +1. I feel really nervous and anxious about meeting people in his life, is this normal?",
  "response": "Yes, it's completely normal to feel nervous and anxious about meeting new people, especially those who are important to your significant other. Here are a few tips to help you manage your anxiety:\n\n1. **Talk to Your Boyfriend:** Express your feelings to your boyfriend. He can provide reassurance and support, and might even give you some background information on the people you'll meet to make you feel more comfortable.\n\n2. **Prepare Mentally:** Remind yourself that everyone at the wedding is there to have a good time and celebrate. They are likely to be friendly and welcoming.\n\n3. **Focus on Positive Outcomes:** Instead of imagining worst-case scenarios, think about positive interactions you might have. This can help reframe your mindset.\n\n4. **Deep Breathing:** Practice deep breathing exercises to calm your nerves. This can be a quick and effective way to reduce anxiety.\n\n5. **Small Talk Tips:** Prepare a few conversation starters or questions you can ask to break the ice. People usually appreciate someone showing interest in them.\n\n6. **Be Yourself:** Remember that your boyfriend likes you for who you are, and his friends and family are likely to see the same qualities.\n\n7. **Take Breaks:** If you start to feel overwhelmed, it\u2019s okay to step outside or find a quiet corner for a few minutes to regroup.\n\n8. **Enjoy the Moment:** Focus on the joy of the occasion and the opportunity to celebrate with your boyfriend.\n\nBy taking these steps, you can help ease your anxiety and enjoy the wedding experience.",
